cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of bidirectional retrieval of images and sentences, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new model that works on a finer level and embeds fragments of images and sentences into a common space, which involves machine learning and deep learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper involves ranking and alignment objectives, which are related to information retrieval and search, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category as well.
